1
00:00:01,251 --> 00:00:04,421
(WHOOSHING)

2
00:00:10,761 --> 00:00:12,596
ROSE: So what is it?
What's wrong?

3
00:00:12,679 --> 00:00:15,766
I don't know. Some kind
of signal, drawing the Tardis off course.

4
00:00:16,099 --> 00:00:17,142
Where are we?

5
00:00:17,226 --> 00:00:19,269
Earth. Utah, North America.

6
00:00:19,686 --> 00:00:21,021
About half a mile underground.

7
00:00:21,104 --> 00:00:23,273
And when are we?

8
00:00:24,274 --> 00:00:25,442
2012.

9
00:00:26,652 --> 00:00:29,112
God, that's so close. I should be 26!

10
00:00:30,614 --> 00:00:32,115
(SWITCH CLICKING)

11
00:00:33,659 --> 00:00:34,701
(WHOOSHING)

12
00:00:34,785 --> 00:00:35,953
Blimey.

13
00:00:36,828 --> 00:00:39,122
ROSE: Like a great big museum.

14
00:00:40,415 --> 00:00:42,084
DOCTOR: An alien museum.

15
00:00:43,544 --> 00:00:45,170
Someone's got a hobby.

16
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:48,382
They must've spent a fortune on this.

17
00:00:49,633 --> 00:00:51,593
Chunks of meteorite. Moondust.

18
00:00:51,927 --> 00:00:53,971
That's the milometer
from the Roswell spaceship.

19
00:00:55,305 --> 00:00:56,598
ROSE:
That's a bit of Slitheen!

20
00:00:56,682 --> 00:00:58,725
That's a Slitheen's arm,
it's been stuffed!

21
00:01:00,686 --> 00:01:02,646
Ah, look at you!

22
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:14,658
What is it?

23
00:01:15,075 --> 00:01:18,078
An old friend of mine. Well, enemy.

24
00:01:19,037 --> 00:01:21,290
The stuff of nightmares,
reduced to an exhibit.

25
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:24,001
I'm getting old.

26
00:01:24,668 --> 00:01:26,336
Is that where the signal's coming from?

27
00:01:26,420 --> 00:01:29,298
Nah, it's stone-dead. The signal's alive.

28
00:01:30,299 --> 00:01:31,717
Something's reaching out.

29
00:01:32,175 --> 00:01:33,510
Calling for help.

30
00:01:36,346 --> 00:01:38,515
(ALARM BUZZING)

31
00:01:49,484 --> 00:01:52,529
If someone's
collecting aliens, that makes you Exhibit A.

32
00:01:55,324 --> 00:01:57,200
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

33
00:02:31,818 --> 00:02:33,236
OFFICER:
Attention all personnel.

34
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:36,657
Bad Wolf 1 descending,
Bad Wolf 1 descending.

35
00:02:45,832 --> 00:02:49,252
On behalf of all of us,
I wanna wish you a very happy birthday, sir.

36
00:02:49,419 --> 00:02:51,797
And the President
called to convey his personal best wishes.

37
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:54,174
The President is
10 points down, I want him replaced.

38
00:02:55,050 --> 00:02:56,760
I don't think that's very wise, sir.

39
00:02:56,843 --> 00:02:58,428
Thank you so much
for your opinion, you're fired.

40
00:02:58,512 --> 00:02:59,805
-Get rid of him.
-What?

41
00:02:59,888 --> 00:03:01,848
Wipe his memory.
Put him on the road someplace.

42
00:03:01,973 --> 00:03:04,601
Memphis, Minneapolis.
Somewhere beginning with "M."

43
00:03:04,726 --> 00:03:07,270
So, the next President, what do you think?
Republican or Democrat?

44
00:03:07,396 --> 00:03:08,939
-Democrat, sir.
-For what reason?

45
00:03:09,731 --> 00:03:11,775
They're just so funny, sir?

46
00:03:13,568 --> 00:03:15,404
-What is your name?
-Goddard, sir.

47
00:03:15,779 --> 00:03:16,947
Diana Goddard.

48
00:03:18,448 --> 00:03:19,825
I like you, Diana Goddard.

49
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:22,619
-So where's the English kid?
-Sir, sir!

50
00:03:23,245 --> 00:03:25,038
I bought 10 more artefacts
at auction, Mr van Statten.

51
00:03:25,122 --> 00:03:26,248
Bring "em on. Let me see 'em.

52
00:03:26,331 --> 00:03:28,417
Uh, sir, with respect,
there's something more urgent.

53
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:32,295
We arrested two intruders, 53 floors down.
We don't know how they got in.

54
00:03:32,379 --> 00:03:34,256
I'll tell you how they got in. In-tru-da window!

55
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:36,508
In-tru-da window, that was funny!

56
00:03:36,675 --> 00:03:37,884
(ALL LAUGH OBEDIENTLY)

57
00:03:37,968 --> 00:03:39,219
Bring 'em in. Let's see 'em.

58
00:03:39,302 --> 00:03:41,722
And tell Simmons I want to visit my little pet.
Get to it.

59
00:03:42,472 --> 00:03:45,559
Simmons, you'd better give me good news!
Is it talking?

60
00:03:45,642 --> 00:03:47,477
(DRILLING)

61
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:56,069
-Not exactly talking, no.
-Then what's it doing?

62
00:03:56,153 --> 00:03:57,154
Screaming.

63
00:03:57,237 --> 00:03:58,572
Is that any good?

64
00:03:58,655 --> 00:04:00,490
(DRILLING RESUMES)

65
00:04:01,158 --> 00:04:02,451
And this is the last.

66
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:04,578
Paid $800,000 for it.

67
00:04:04,911 --> 00:04:05,912
What does it do?

68
00:04:06,663 --> 00:04:08,582
Well, you see the tubes on the side?

69
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:11,084
Must be to channel something,
I think maybe fuel.

70
00:04:11,168 --> 00:04:12,544
I really wouldn't hold it like that.

71
00:04:12,627 --> 00:04:15,130
-Shut it!
-Really though, that's wrong.

72
00:04:15,714 --> 00:04:16,923
Is it dangerous?

73
00:04:17,007 --> 00:04:18,383
No, it just looks silly.

74
00:04:18,842 --> 00:04:20,177
(GUNS COCKING)

75
00:04:29,352 --> 00:04:30,937
You just need to be...

76
00:04:31,396 --> 00:04:32,689
(INSTRUMENT HUMS)

77
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:35,150
...delicate.

78
00:04:36,443 --> 00:04:37,903
(HUM CHANGES TONE)

79
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:43,116
It's a musical instrument.

80
00:04:45,827 --> 00:04:47,037
And it's a long way from home.

81
00:04:47,496 --> 00:04:48,538
Here, let me.

82
00:04:50,415 --> 00:04:51,666
I did say delicate.

83
00:04:52,542 --> 00:04:55,003
DOCTOR: It reacts to the
smallest fingerprint.

84
00:04:56,004 --> 00:04:57,214
It needs precision.

85
00:04:58,256 --> 00:04:59,883
(INSTRUMENT HUMS)

86
00:05:02,344 --> 00:05:04,554
Very good. Quite the expert.

87
00:05:05,430 --> 00:05:06,473
As are you.

88
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:09,476
-(INSTRUMENT CLATTERS)
-Who exactly are you?

89
00:05:11,186 --> 00:05:12,562
I'm the Doctor. And who are you?

90
00:05:12,687 --> 00:05:13,814
Like you don't know!

91
00:05:14,272 --> 00:05:16,650
We're hidden away with the
most valuable collection

92
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:19,569
of extraterrestrial artefacts in the world,

93
00:05:19,694 --> 00:05:22,239
and you just stumbled in by mistake.

94
00:05:22,364 --> 00:05:24,324
(CHUCKLING) Pretty much
sums me up, yeah.

95
00:05:24,741 --> 00:05:26,243
Question is, how did you get in?

96
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:30,789
53 floors down, with your
little cat-burglar accomplice.

97
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:32,999
Quite a collector yourself, she's rather pretty.

98
00:05:33,083 --> 00:05:35,585
She's gonna smack you
if you keep calling her "she."

99
00:05:35,919 --> 00:05:37,587
She's English, too!

100
00:05:37,796 --> 00:05:40,006
Hey, Little Lord Fauntleroy,
got you a girlfriend.

101
00:05:40,757 --> 00:05:42,467
This is Mr Henry van Statten.

102
00:05:42,968 --> 00:05:44,219
And who's he when he's at home?

103
00:05:44,302 --> 00:05:46,096
Mr an Statten owns the internet.

104
00:05:46,429 --> 00:05:48,849
Don't be stupid. No one owns the Internet.

105
00:05:48,932 --> 00:05:51,601
Let's just keep the
whole world thinking that way, right, kids?

106
00:05:52,018 --> 00:05:54,145
So you're just about an expert in everything,

107
00:05:54,229 --> 00:05:55,272
except the things in your museum.

108
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:57,190
Anything you don't understand, you lock up.

109
00:05:57,274 --> 00:05:58,525
And you claim greater knowledge?

110
00:05:58,608 --> 00:06:00,443
I don't need to make claims.
I know how good I am.

111
00:06:00,569 --> 00:06:03,446
And yet I captured you right next to the Cage.

112
00:06:04,239 --> 00:06:05,365
What were you doing down there?

113
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:06,449
You tell me.

114
00:06:06,575 --> 00:06:09,369
The Cage contains my one living specimen.

115
00:06:09,452 --> 00:06:10,954
-And what's that?
-Like you don't know.

116
00:06:11,037 --> 00:06:12,455
-Show me.
-You wanna see it?

117
00:06:13,039 --> 00:06:14,958
Blimey, you can smell the testosterone.

118
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:18,378
Goddard! Inform the Cage
we're heading down.

119
00:06:18,587 --> 00:06:20,255
You, English, look after the girl.

120
00:06:20,338 --> 00:06:23,717
Go and canoodle or spoon
or whatever it is you British do.

121
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:26,094
And you, Doctor with no name.

122
00:06:27,721 --> 00:06:29,180
Come and see my pet!

123
00:06:32,434 --> 00:06:34,019
We've tried everything.

124
00:06:34,352 --> 00:06:39,941
The creature has shielded
itself, but there's definite signs of life inside.

125
00:06:40,358 --> 00:06:41,985
Inside? Inside what?

126
00:06:42,068 --> 00:06:43,069
SIMMONS: Welcome back, sir!

127
00:06:43,653 --> 00:06:46,489
I've had to take
the power down, the Metaltron is resting.

128
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:47,824
Metaltron?

129
00:06:48,158 --> 00:06:50,160
Thought of it myself. Good, isn't it?

130
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:53,121
Although I'd much prefer
to find out its real name.

131
00:06:53,330 --> 00:06:55,123
Here, you'd better put these on.

132
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:56,666
The last guy that touched it

133
00:06:58,043 --> 00:06:59,252
burst into flames.

134
00:07:00,170 --> 00:07:01,379
I won't touch it, then.

135
00:07:03,131 --> 00:07:04,466
Go ahead, Doctor.

136
00:07:04,549 --> 00:07:05,842
Impress me.

137
00:07:17,479 --> 00:07:20,106
Don't open that door until we get a result.

138
00:07:29,366 --> 00:07:30,784
(DOOR SLAMS)

139
00:07:34,913 --> 00:07:36,164
Look, I'm sorry about this.

140
00:07:36,247 --> 00:07:39,250
Mr van Statten
might think he's clever, but never mind him.

141
00:07:39,626 --> 00:07:41,795
I've come to help. I'm the Doctor.

142
00:07:43,213 --> 00:07:45,340
MECHANICAL VOICE: Doctor.

143
00:07:47,217 --> 00:07:48,426
Impossible!

144
00:07:49,427 --> 00:07:51,429
The Doctor?

145
00:07:54,891 --> 00:07:56,559
Exterminate!

146
00:07:56,893 --> 00:07:58,395
Exterminate!

147
00:07:58,603 --> 00:07:59,646
DOCTOR: Let me out!

148
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:00,897
Exterminate!

149
00:08:01,731 --> 00:08:03,900
-Sir, it's going to kill him!
-It's talking!

150
00:08:03,984 --> 00:08:06,736
You are an enemy of the Daleks.

151
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:09,322
You must be destroyed!

152
00:08:13,535 --> 00:08:14,911
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

153
00:08:15,537 --> 00:08:17,247
It's not working.

154
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:20,917
(LAUGHING)

155
00:08:24,879 --> 00:08:26,256
Fantastic!

156
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,633
Oh, fantastic!

157
00:08:30,051 --> 00:08:31,928
DOCTOR: Powerless.
Look at you.

158
00:08:32,762 --> 00:08:35,807
The great space dustbin. How does it feel?

159
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:37,392
DALEK: Keep back!

160
00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:38,601
What for?

161
00:08:38,727 --> 00:08:40,270
What are you gonna do to me?

162
00:08:44,733 --> 00:08:46,568
If you can't kill,

163
00:08:48,528 --> 00:08:50,447
then what are you good for, Dalek?

164
00:08:51,281 --> 00:08:53,283
What's the point of you?

165
00:08:55,952 --> 00:08:57,620
You're nothing.

166
00:08:58,455 --> 00:08:59,998
DOCTOR: What the hell
are you here for?

167
00:09:00,206 --> 00:09:03,918
DALEK:
I am waiting for orders.

168
00:09:04,002 --> 00:09:07,255
-What does that mean?
-I am a soldier.

169
00:09:07,338 --> 00:09:10,717
I was bred to receive orders.

170
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:13,219
Well, you're never gonna get any. Not ever.

171
00:09:13,303 --> 00:09:15,597
I demand orders!

172
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:18,224
They're never gonna come. Your race is dead.

173
00:09:18,308 --> 00:09:21,436
You all burnt. All of you.
Ten million ships on fire.

174
00:09:21,519 --> 00:09:25,148
The entire Dalek race
wiped out, in one second.

175
00:09:25,315 --> 00:09:26,483
You lie!

176
00:09:26,608 --> 00:09:27,692
I watched it happen.

177
00:09:27,776 --> 00:09:28,985
I made it happen.

178
00:09:29,152 --> 00:09:31,446
You destroyed us?

179
00:09:41,873 --> 00:09:43,500
I had no choice.

180
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:48,129
And what of the Time Lords?

181
00:09:53,510 --> 00:09:54,761
Dead.

182
00:09:55,220 --> 00:09:57,097
They burnt with you.

183
00:09:57,222 --> 00:09:59,766
The end of the Last Great Time War.

184
00:10:01,351 --> 00:10:02,852
Everyone lost.

185
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:08,441
And the coward survived.

186
00:10:08,525 --> 00:10:11,778
Oh, and I caught your little signal.

187
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:15,615
"Help me." Poor little thing.

188
00:10:18,118 --> 00:10:21,371
But there's no one else
coming 'cause there's no one else left.

189
00:10:21,913 --> 00:10:27,877
I am alone in the universe.

190
00:10:28,419 --> 00:10:30,380
Yep. (LAUGHS)

191
00:10:32,090 --> 00:10:34,676
So are you.

192
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:39,514
We are the same.

193
00:10:40,056 --> 00:10:42,392
We're not the same! I'm not...

194
00:10:44,060 --> 00:10:45,562
No, wait.

195
00:10:46,688 --> 00:10:48,231
Maybe we are.

196
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:50,525
You're right! Yeah, okay!

197
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:52,527
You've got a point.

198
00:10:52,986 --> 00:10:54,279
'Cause I know what to do.

199
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:56,656
I know what should happen.

200
00:10:57,240 --> 00:10:58,867
I know what you deserve.

201
00:11:02,078 --> 00:11:03,454
Exterminate.

202
00:11:05,248 --> 00:11:06,541
(DALEK SCREAMING)

203
00:11:07,125 --> 00:11:08,960
Have pity!

204
00:11:09,043 --> 00:11:11,254
Why should I? You never did!

205
00:11:12,463 --> 00:11:13,590
Get him out!

206
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:15,842
Help me!

207
00:11:17,510 --> 00:11:19,053
HENRY: I saved your life.

208
00:11:19,179 --> 00:11:21,890
Now talk to me. God damn it, talk to me!

209
00:11:21,973 --> 00:11:23,600
DOCTOR:
You've got to destroy it!

210
00:11:24,225 --> 00:11:26,311
HENRY:
The last in the universe.

211
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:28,938
And now I know your name.

212
00:11:29,606 --> 00:11:30,982
Dalek.

213
00:11:31,441 --> 00:11:33,276
Speak to me, Dalek!

214
00:11:34,819 --> 00:11:38,156
I am Henry van Statten,
now recognise me!

215
00:11:42,952 --> 00:11:45,288
Make it talk again, Simmons.

216
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:47,707
Whatever it takes.

217
00:11:51,628 --> 00:11:53,171
ADAM: Sorry about the mess.

218
00:11:53,254 --> 00:11:55,840
Mr van Statten sort of lets me
do my own thing,

219
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:58,551
so long as I deliver the goods.

220
00:11:59,135 --> 00:12:01,930
What do you think that is?

221
00:12:06,017 --> 00:12:07,018
Uhh.

222
00:12:07,143 --> 00:12:09,312
-A lump of metal?
-Yeah.

223
00:12:09,729 --> 00:12:10,772
Yeah, but I think...

224
00:12:10,897 --> 00:12:14,609
Well, I'm almost certain,
it's from the hull of a spacecraft.

225
00:12:15,485 --> 00:12:20,073
The thing is, it's all true, everything the
United Nations tries to keep quiet.

226
00:12:21,032 --> 00:12:23,993
Spacecraft, aliens, visitors to Earth.

227
00:12:24,994 --> 00:12:26,120
They really exist.

228
00:12:26,412 --> 00:12:27,497
That's amazing.

229
00:12:27,664 --> 00:12:28,873
I know it sounds incredible.

230
00:12:28,998 --> 00:12:32,627
But I honestly believe
the whole universe is just teeming with life.

231
00:12:33,002 --> 00:12:34,921
I'm gobsmacked, yeah.

232
00:12:36,130 --> 00:12:38,466
And you do what? Sit here and catalogue it?

233
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:40,677
Best job in the world!

234
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:43,179
Imagine if you could get out there.

235
00:12:43,263 --> 00:12:45,890
Travel amongst the stars and see it for real.

236
00:12:46,099 --> 00:12:48,268
Yeah. I'd give anything.

237
00:12:48,851 --> 00:12:51,104
I don't think it's ever gonna happen.
Not in our lifetimes.

238
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:52,313
Oh, you never know.

239
00:12:52,605 --> 00:12:55,817
What about all those people who say they've
been inside of spaceships and things,

240
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:57,527
and talked to aliens?

241
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:00,530
I think they're nutters.

242
00:13:01,197 --> 00:13:02,365
Yeah. Me, too.

243
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:03,700
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

244
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:06,786
So how do you end up here?

245
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,997
Van Statten has agents all over the world,

246
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:10,123
looking for geniuses to recruit.

247
00:13:10,206 --> 00:13:12,125
Oh, right, you're a genius.

248
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:13,918
Sorry, but, yeah.

249
00:13:14,002 --> 00:13:15,920
I can't help it, I was born clever.

250
00:13:17,213 --> 00:13:20,091
When I was eight,
I logged onto the US defence system.

251
00:13:20,466 --> 00:13:22,051
Nearly caused World War Three.

252
00:13:22,135 --> 00:13:23,428
What, and that's funny, is it?

253
00:13:23,553 --> 00:13:26,306
You should've been there.
Just to see them running about.

254
00:13:26,389 --> 00:13:27,515
Fantastic!

255
00:13:29,225 --> 00:13:30,810
You sound like the Doctor.

256
00:13:31,227 --> 00:13:33,313
-Are you and him...
-No, we're just friends.

257
00:13:33,438 --> 00:13:34,522
Good.

258
00:13:35,106 --> 00:13:36,399
Why's that good?

259
00:13:36,899 --> 00:13:38,276
Just is.

260
00:13:41,070 --> 00:13:45,325
So, wouldn't you rather be downstairs?

261
00:13:45,408 --> 00:13:47,994
You've got these bits of metal and stuff,

262
00:13:48,411 --> 00:13:50,496
but Mr van Statten's got
a living creature down there.

263
00:13:50,580 --> 00:13:53,833
Yeah. Well, I did ask,
but he keeps it to himself.

264
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:57,170
Although, if you're a genius,

265
00:13:57,253 --> 00:13:59,714
it doesn't take long to patch
through on the comms system.

266
00:14:00,590 --> 00:14:02,091
(LAUGHING) Let's have a look then!

267
00:14:04,927 --> 00:14:07,555
It doesn't do much, the alien.

268
00:14:08,181 --> 00:14:10,933
It's weird, it's kind of useless.

269
00:14:11,017 --> 00:14:14,270
It's just like this great big pepper pot.

270
00:14:20,651 --> 00:14:22,111
-(DRILLING)
-(DALEK SCREAMING)

271
00:14:25,615 --> 00:14:27,116
It's being tortured. Where's the Doctor?

272
00:14:28,117 --> 00:14:30,119
-I don't know.
-Take me down there. Now.

273
00:14:32,288 --> 00:14:33,414
The metal's just battle arm our.

274
00:14:33,498 --> 00:14:35,041
The real Dalek creature is inside.

275
00:14:35,124 --> 00:14:36,626
-What does it look like?
-A nightmare.

276
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:39,670
It's a mutation.
The Dalek race were genetically engineered.

277
00:14:39,754 --> 00:14:42,173
Every single emotion
was removed, except hate.

278
00:14:42,256 --> 00:14:45,426
Genetically engineered? By whom?

279
00:14:45,510 --> 00:14:46,803
By a genius, van Statten.

280
00:14:47,053 --> 00:14:49,639
By a man who was
king of his own little world. You'd like him.

281
00:14:49,722 --> 00:14:51,724
It's been on Earth for over 50 years.

282
00:14:51,808 --> 00:14:55,103
Sold at private auction,
moving from one collection to another.

283
00:14:55,186 --> 00:14:56,437
Why would it be a threat now?

284
00:14:56,521 --> 00:14:59,273
Because I'm here. How did it get to Earth?
Does anyone know?

285
00:14:59,357 --> 00:15:01,901
The records say it came
from the sky like a meteorite.

286
00:15:01,984 --> 00:15:04,070
It fell to Earth on the Ascension Islands,

287
00:15:04,153 --> 00:15:05,655
burnt in its crater for three days,

288
00:15:05,738 --> 00:15:06,906
before anybody could get near it.

289
00:15:06,989 --> 00:15:10,326
And all that time, it was screaming.
Must have gone insane.

290
00:15:12,954 --> 00:15:15,415
It must have fallen through time.
The only survivor.

291
00:15:15,498 --> 00:15:16,624
You talked about a war?

292
00:15:16,707 --> 00:15:20,420
The Time War. The final battle
between my people and the Dalek race.

293
00:15:20,628 --> 00:15:22,046
But you survived, too.

294
00:15:22,672 --> 00:15:23,798
Not by choice.

295
00:15:23,881 --> 00:15:27,969
This means the Dalek
isn't the only alien on Earth, Doctor.

296
00:15:28,052 --> 00:15:29,053
There's you.

297
00:15:29,137 --> 00:15:32,348
The only one of your kind in existence.

298
00:15:42,692 --> 00:15:44,277
Now smile!

299
00:15:45,027 --> 00:15:46,487
(MACHINE BLASTS)

300
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:47,864
(GROANING)

301
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:51,075
HENRY: Two hearts.

302
00:15:51,159 --> 00:15:52,702
A binary vascular system!

303
00:15:52,869 --> 00:15:54,537
Oh, I am so gonna patent this.

304
00:15:54,871 --> 00:15:56,372
So that's your secret.

305
00:15:56,497 --> 00:15:58,791
You don't just collect
this stuff, you scavenge it.

306
00:15:58,875 --> 00:16:02,753
This technology
has been falling to Earth for centuries.

307
00:16:02,837 --> 00:16:06,174
All it took was the right mind
to use it properly.

308
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:10,386
Oh, the advances I've made from alien junk.

309
00:16:10,470 --> 00:16:12,180
You have no idea, Doctor!

310
00:16:12,263 --> 00:16:14,056
Broadband? Roswell.

311
00:16:14,849 --> 00:16:18,978
Just last year, my scientists
cultivated bacteria

312
00:16:19,061 --> 00:16:21,772
from the Russian crater,
and do you know what we found?

313
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:25,026
The cure for the common cold.

314
00:16:27,069 --> 00:16:30,907
Kept it strictly within the laboratory, of
course. No need to get people excited.

315
00:16:31,032 --> 00:16:34,869
Why sell one cure
when I can sell a thousand palliatives?

316
00:16:34,952 --> 00:16:37,079
Do you know what a Dalek is, van Statten?

317
00:16:39,165 --> 00:16:40,500
A Dalek is honest.

318
00:16:40,583 --> 00:16:43,920
It does what it was
born to do, for the survival of its species.

319
00:16:44,003 --> 00:16:46,339
That creature in your dungeon
is better than you.

320
00:16:46,756 --> 00:16:49,050
In that case,
I will be true to myself.

321
00:16:49,592 --> 00:16:50,927
And continue.

322
00:16:51,552 --> 00:16:55,598
Listen to me! That thing
downstairs is gonna kill every last one of us!

323
00:16:55,681 --> 00:16:57,350
Nothing can escape the Cage.

324
00:16:57,892 --> 00:17:00,269
(MACHINE BLASTS)

325
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:04,315
DOCTOR: But it's woken up!
It knows I'm here! It's gonna get out!

326
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:07,985
Van Statten, I swear,
no one on this base is safe.

327
00:17:08,194 --> 00:17:09,445
No one on this planet!

328
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:11,072
(MACHINE BLASTS)

329
00:17:11,239 --> 00:17:12,448
(SCREAMING)

330
00:17:13,324 --> 00:17:15,034
Hold it right there. Level three access.

331
00:17:15,117 --> 00:17:17,203
Special clearance from Mr van Statten.

332
00:17:21,374 --> 00:17:23,209
Don't get too close.

333
00:17:36,389 --> 00:17:37,431
Hello?

334
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:41,227
Are you in pain?

335
00:17:41,352 --> 00:17:42,728
My name's Rose Tyler.

336
00:17:42,812 --> 00:17:44,897
I've got a friend, he can help.
He's called the Doctor.

337
00:17:44,981 --> 00:17:46,315
What's your name?

338
00:17:46,816 --> 00:17:48,025
Yes.

339
00:17:49,318 --> 00:17:50,319
What?

340
00:17:52,989 --> 00:17:55,992
I am in pain.

341
00:17:57,243 --> 00:17:59,662
They torture me,

342
00:18:00,997 --> 00:18:05,334
but still they fear me.

343
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:08,296
Do you fear me?

344
00:18:10,214 --> 00:18:11,340
No.

345
00:18:15,428 --> 00:18:19,140
I am dying.

346
00:18:19,307 --> 00:18:20,933
No, we can help.

347
00:18:21,892 --> 00:18:24,937
I welcome death.

348
00:18:26,147 --> 00:18:28,941
But I am glad

349
00:18:30,610 --> 00:18:33,904
that before I die,

350
00:18:35,197 --> 00:18:38,159
I met a human

351
00:18:38,242 --> 00:18:41,621
who was not afraid.

352
00:18:42,538 --> 00:18:44,665
Isn't there anything I can do?

353
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:48,711
My race is dead.

354
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:53,883
I shall die alone.

355
00:19:03,059 --> 00:19:04,352
-ADAM: Rose, no!
-(MACHINE SEETHES)

356
00:19:06,312 --> 00:19:11,192
Genetic material extrapolated.

357
00:19:11,275 --> 00:19:15,988
Initiate cellular reconstruction!

358
00:19:23,079 --> 00:19:24,580
What the hell have you done?

359
00:19:28,584 --> 00:19:31,504
What ya gonna do? Sucker me to death?

360
00:19:31,587 --> 00:19:33,339
(MUFFLED SCREAM)

361
00:19:35,716 --> 00:19:36,967
It's killing him! Do something!

362
00:19:37,093 --> 00:19:38,135
Condition red. Condition red.

363
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:39,637
I repeat, this is not a drill!

364
00:19:41,389 --> 00:19:43,432
Release me if you want to live.

365
00:19:46,185 --> 00:19:47,603
You've got to keep it in that cell!

366
00:19:47,978 --> 00:19:49,146
Doctor, it's all my fault.

367
00:19:49,271 --> 00:19:50,690
I've sealed the compartment.

368
00:19:50,773 --> 00:19:52,692
It can't get out.
That lock's got a billion combinations.

369
00:19:52,775 --> 00:19:53,776
DOCTOR: The Dalek's a genius.

370
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:57,613
It can calculate a thousand
billion combinations in one second flat.

371
00:20:18,968 --> 00:20:20,261
Open fire!

372
00:20:22,179 --> 00:20:23,723
HENRY: Don't shoot it.
I want it unharmed!

373
00:20:24,140 --> 00:20:25,349
Rose, get out of there!

374
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:27,309
(GUNSHOTS)

375
00:20:33,649 --> 00:20:36,235
De Maggio, take the civilians
and get them out alive.

376
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:37,653
That is your job, got that?

377
00:20:38,112 --> 00:20:39,280
You! With me!

378
00:20:49,331 --> 00:20:51,000
(ELECTRICAL BUZZ)

379
00:20:58,966 --> 00:21:00,718
Abandoning the Cage, sir!

380
00:21:01,927 --> 00:21:04,847
We're losing power. It's draining the base.

381
00:21:04,930 --> 00:21:06,140
Oh, my God.

382
00:21:06,223 --> 00:21:08,768
It's draining the entire
power supplies of the whole of Utah.

383
00:21:08,851 --> 00:21:10,686
-It's downloading.
-Downloading what?

384
00:21:11,312 --> 00:21:13,522
Sir! The entire West Coast has gone down!

385
00:21:13,606 --> 00:21:17,526
It's not just energy.
That Dalek just absorbed the entire Internet.

386
00:21:17,610 --> 00:21:19,111
It knows everything!

387
00:21:20,696 --> 00:21:25,075
The Daleks survive in me!

388
00:21:34,877 --> 00:21:36,337
The cameras in the vault have gone down.

389
00:21:36,420 --> 00:21:38,798
We've only got emergency power.
It's eaten everything else.

390
00:21:38,881 --> 00:21:40,216
You've got to kill it now!

391
00:21:40,299 --> 00:21:42,551
All guards to converge on the
Metaltron Cage immediately.

392
00:21:44,804 --> 00:21:46,263
Civilians! Let 'em through!

393
00:21:51,060 --> 00:21:52,478
Cover the north wall.

394
00:21:52,561 --> 00:21:55,189
Red division, maintain
suppressing fire along the perimeter.

395
00:21:55,272 --> 00:21:57,358
Blue division... (GROANS)

396
00:21:57,441 --> 00:21:58,692
(GUNSHOTS)

397
00:22:08,536 --> 00:22:09,829
(SCREAMING)

398
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:17,753
(SCREAMS)

399
00:22:23,467 --> 00:22:24,510
(SOLDIER SCREAMING)

400
00:22:28,889 --> 00:22:30,224
Tell them to stop shooting at it.

401
00:22:30,307 --> 00:22:31,433
But it's killing them!

402
00:22:31,517 --> 00:22:34,353
They're dispensable, that Dalek is unique.

403
00:22:34,436 --> 00:22:37,982
I don't want a scratch on its bodywork!
Do you hear me?

404
00:22:39,066 --> 00:22:40,651
Do you hear me?

405
00:22:40,943 --> 00:22:42,736
(GUNSHOTS DIE OUT)

406
00:22:57,126 --> 00:22:59,003
GODDARD: That's us,
right below the surface.

407
00:22:59,128 --> 00:23:01,422
That's the Cage, and that's the Dalek.

408
00:23:01,505 --> 00:23:03,799
This museum of yours.
Have you got any alien weapons?

409
00:23:03,883 --> 00:23:06,468
Lots of them, but the trouble is
the Dalek's between us and them.

410
00:23:06,677 --> 00:23:08,053
We've got to keep that thing alive.

411
00:23:08,137 --> 00:23:10,097
We could just
seal the entire vault, trap it down there.

412
00:23:10,222 --> 00:23:11,432
Leaving everyone trapped with it?

413
00:23:11,515 --> 00:23:14,518
Rose is down there.
I won't let that happen, have you got that?

414
00:23:15,144 --> 00:23:16,812
It has to go through this area. What's that?

415
00:23:17,062 --> 00:23:18,147
GODDARD: Weapons testing.

416
00:23:18,230 --> 00:23:20,983
Give guns to technicians,
the lawyers, anyone, everyone.

417
00:23:21,066 --> 00:23:23,402
Only then have you got a chance of killing it.

418
00:23:25,613 --> 00:23:27,531
Stairs! That's more like it!

419
00:23:27,615 --> 00:23:28,824
Hasn't got legs, it's stuck!

420
00:23:28,908 --> 00:23:30,409
It's coming! Get up!

421
00:23:46,342 --> 00:23:48,552
ADAM: Great big alien
death machine.

422
00:23:48,636 --> 00:23:50,804
Defeated by a flight of stairs!

423
00:23:52,598 --> 00:23:53,641
DE MAGGIO: Now listen to me.

424
00:23:54,516 --> 00:23:56,602
I demand that you return to your Cage.

425
00:23:56,685 --> 00:23:57,937
If you want to negotiate,

426
00:23:58,020 --> 00:24:00,522
then I can guarantee
Mr van Statten will be willing to talk.

427
00:24:00,606 --> 00:24:02,316
I accept that we imprisoned you,

428
00:24:02,399 --> 00:24:04,026
and maybe that was wrong,

429
00:24:04,151 --> 00:24:07,613
but people have died,
and that stops right now.

430
00:24:08,739 --> 00:24:10,866
The killing stops. Have you got that?

431
00:24:11,367 --> 00:24:13,452
I demand that you surrender. Is that clear?

432
00:24:15,037 --> 00:24:17,247
Elevate.

433
00:24:24,505 --> 00:24:26,090
Oh, my God.

434
00:24:32,096 --> 00:24:33,514
Adam, get her out of here.

435
00:24:35,933 --> 00:24:37,226
Come with us. You can't stop it.

436
00:24:37,309 --> 00:24:39,937
Someone's got to try. Now get out!

437
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:42,106
Don't look back, just run!

438
00:24:43,774 --> 00:24:45,234
(GUNSHOTS)

439
00:24:50,864 --> 00:24:52,324
(DE MAGGIO SCREAMING)

440
00:24:52,408 --> 00:24:53,826
(PANTING)

441
00:24:54,910 --> 00:24:56,954
I thought you were the great expert, Doctor.

442
00:24:57,329 --> 00:25:00,624
If you're so impressive,
then why not just reason with this Dalek?

443
00:25:01,250 --> 00:25:02,459
It must be willing to negotiate.

444
00:25:02,543 --> 00:25:04,253
There must be something it needs.

445
00:25:04,336 --> 00:25:05,379
Everything needs something.

446
00:25:05,462 --> 00:25:07,172
-What's the nearest town?
-Salt Lake City.

447
00:25:07,256 --> 00:25:08,507
-Population?
-One million.

448
00:25:08,590 --> 00:25:09,675
All dead.

449
00:25:09,758 --> 00:25:12,052
If the Dalek gets out,
it'll murder every living creature.

450
00:25:12,136 --> 00:25:14,013
-That's all it needs.
-But why would it do that?

451
00:25:14,096 --> 00:25:15,681
Because it honestly believes they should die.

452
00:26:38,847 --> 00:26:40,224
Yeah, it wants to slaughter us!

453
00:26:40,349 --> 00:26:42,101
No, but it was looking right at me!

454
00:26:42,184 --> 00:26:46,021
So? It's just a sort
of metal eye thing, it's looking all around.

455
00:26:46,563 --> 00:26:47,648
I don't know. It's like,

456
00:26:47,731 --> 00:26:50,442
it's like there's
something inside, looking at me.

457
00:26:50,526 --> 00:26:53,237
Like, like it knows me.

458
00:26:59,368 --> 00:27:00,536
On my mark.

459
00:27:06,750 --> 00:27:07,835
Open fire!

460
00:27:08,293 --> 00:27:09,711
(GUNSHOTS)

461
00:27:15,384 --> 00:27:16,760
We've got vision!

462
00:27:21,849 --> 00:27:22,975
It wants us to see.

463
00:27:37,281 --> 00:27:38,574
(GUNSHOTS CONTINUE)

464
00:28:17,279 --> 00:28:18,572
(ALL SCREAMING)

465
00:28:27,873 --> 00:28:29,124
Fall back! Fall back!

466
00:28:59,321 --> 00:29:01,031
Perhaps it's time for a new strategy.

467
00:29:01,114 --> 00:29:03,367
Maybe we should consider
abandoning this place.

468
00:29:03,450 --> 00:29:06,328
Except there's no power to the helipad, sir.

469
00:29:06,411 --> 00:29:07,955
We can't get out.

470
00:29:08,038 --> 00:29:09,581
You said we could seal the vault?

471
00:29:09,998 --> 00:29:13,752
It was designed to be a bunker
in the event of nuclear war.

472
00:29:13,835 --> 00:29:15,128
-Steel bulkheads...
-There's not enough power!

473
00:29:15,212 --> 00:29:17,464
-Those bulkheads are massive.
-DOCTOR: We've got emergency power,

474
00:29:17,547 --> 00:29:18,757
we can reroute that to the bulkhead door.

475
00:29:18,840 --> 00:29:20,175
We'd have to bypass the security codes.

476
00:29:20,300 --> 00:29:21,760
That would take a computer genius.

477
00:29:21,843 --> 00:29:22,886
Good thing you've got me, then.

478
00:29:22,970 --> 00:29:26,139
-You wanna help?
-I don't want to die, Doctor, simple as that.

479
00:29:26,223 --> 00:29:29,142
And nobody knows this software
better than me.

480
00:29:29,226 --> 00:29:30,352
Sir?

481
00:29:31,311 --> 00:29:36,525
I shall speak only to the Doctor.

482
00:29:41,196 --> 00:29:42,864
You're gonna get rusty.

483
00:29:42,990 --> 00:29:49,079
I fed off the DNA of Rose Tyler.

484
00:29:49,204 --> 00:29:55,085
Extrapolating the biomass of a time traveller

485
00:29:55,168 --> 00:29:57,629
regenerated me.

486
00:29:57,713 --> 00:29:58,880
What's your next trick?

487
00:29:59,339 --> 00:30:03,885
I have been searching for the Daleks.

488
00:30:04,094 --> 00:30:05,470
Yeah, I saw.

489
00:30:06,054 --> 00:30:08,557
Downloading the Internet.
What did you find?

490
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:13,854
I scanned your satellites
and radio telescopes.

491
00:30:14,229 --> 00:30:15,230
And?

492
00:30:15,731 --> 00:30:17,065
Nothing.

493
00:30:18,108 --> 00:30:20,986
Where shall I get my orders now?

494
00:30:21,236 --> 00:30:23,238
You're just a soldier without commands.

495
00:30:23,572 --> 00:30:27,701
Then I shall follow the Primary Order.

496
00:30:27,784 --> 00:30:32,372
The Dalek instinct to destroy. To conquer!

497
00:30:32,456 --> 00:30:34,041
What for? What's the point?

498
00:30:37,586 --> 00:30:39,379
Don't you see? It's all gone.

499
00:30:39,463 --> 00:30:42,257
Everything you were,
everything you stood for.

500
00:30:44,092 --> 00:30:46,970
Then what should I do?

501
00:30:49,389 --> 00:30:50,891
All right, then.

502
00:30:51,641 --> 00:30:54,186
If you want orders, follow this one.

503
00:30:57,731 --> 00:30:58,815
Kill yourself.

504
00:30:58,940 --> 00:31:01,026
The Daleks must survive!

505
00:31:01,109 --> 00:31:02,527
The Daleks have failed!

506
00:31:02,611 --> 00:31:05,447
Why don't you finish the job
and make the Daleks extinct?

507
00:31:05,614 --> 00:31:07,240
Rid the universe of your filth!

508
00:31:07,407 --> 00:31:08,867
Why don't you just die?

509
00:31:11,828 --> 00:31:15,916
You would make a good Dalek.

510
00:31:23,090 --> 00:31:24,466
Seal the vaults.

511
00:31:33,809 --> 00:31:37,145
I can leech power off the ground
defences, feed it to the bulkheads.

512
00:31:37,521 --> 00:31:39,231
It's been years since I had to work this fast!

513
00:31:39,314 --> 00:31:40,941
-Are you enjoying this?
-GODDARD: Doctor.

514
00:31:41,024 --> 00:31:42,025
She's still down there.

515
00:31:42,150 --> 00:31:43,443
(CELLULAR PHONE RINGING)

516
00:31:46,488 --> 00:31:47,697
ROSE:
This isn't the best time!

517
00:31:47,948 --> 00:31:50,117
-DOCTOR: Where are you?
-Level 49.

518
00:31:50,742 --> 00:31:54,329
You've got to keep moving.
The vault is being sealed off up at level 46.

519
00:31:54,454 --> 00:31:55,914
Can't you stop them closing?

520
00:31:55,997 --> 00:31:57,124
I'm the one who's closing them.

521
00:31:57,207 --> 00:31:58,834
I can't wait, and I can't help you.

522
00:31:58,917 --> 00:32:00,877
Now for God's sake, run/

523
00:32:09,010 --> 00:32:10,762
Done it! We've got power to the bulkheads.

524
00:32:10,846 --> 00:32:12,472
GODDARD: The Dalek's
right behind them.

525
00:32:13,056 --> 00:32:14,724
We're nearly there! Give us two seconds!

526
00:32:15,100 --> 00:32:16,435
Doctor, I can't sustain the power.

527
00:32:16,518 --> 00:32:18,103
The whole system is failing.

528
00:32:18,186 --> 00:32:19,855
Doctor, you've got to close the bulkheads.

529
00:32:29,781 --> 00:32:30,866
I'm sorry.

530
00:32:33,452 --> 00:32:34,995
(DOORS BLEEP)

531
00:32:37,789 --> 00:32:38,957
Come on!

532
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:40,834
(DOORS BLEEP FASTER)

533
00:33:00,228 --> 00:33:01,396
The vault is sealed.

534
00:33:02,189 --> 00:33:04,774
Rose! Where are you? Rose, did you make it?

535
00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:06,735
(PANTS)

536
00:33:10,197 --> 00:33:11,781
Sorry. I was a bit slow.

537
00:33:23,502 --> 00:33:25,420
See you, then, Doctor.

538
00:33:30,091 --> 00:33:31,676
It wasn't your fault.

539
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:33,845
Remember that, okay? It wasn't your fault.

540
00:33:35,805 --> 00:33:37,057
And do you know what?

541
00:33:38,517 --> 00:33:41,311
I wouldn't have missed it for the world.

542
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:53,240
DALEK: Exterminate!

543
00:33:53,323 --> 00:33:54,783
(ELECTRICAL PULSE)

544
00:33:58,245 --> 00:33:59,412
I killed her.

545
00:33:59,496 --> 00:34:00,580
I'm sorry.

546
00:34:02,123 --> 00:34:04,042
I said I'd protect her.

547
00:34:04,417 --> 00:34:06,670
She was only here
because of me, and you're sorry?

548
00:34:06,753 --> 00:34:10,632
I could have killed
that Dalek in its cell, but you stopped me.

549
00:34:10,715 --> 00:34:12,425
It was the prize of my collection!

550
00:34:12,509 --> 00:34:15,178
Your collection? Well, was it worth it?

551
00:34:15,595 --> 00:34:18,139
Worth all those men's deaths? Worth Rose?

552
00:34:18,848 --> 00:34:20,433
Let me tell you something, van Statten.

553
00:34:20,517 --> 00:34:22,811
Mankind goes into space to explore.

554
00:34:22,936 --> 00:34:24,312
To be part of something greater...

555
00:34:24,396 --> 00:34:27,440
Exactly! I wanted to touch the stars.

556
00:34:27,524 --> 00:34:30,151
You just want to drag the stars
down and stick them underground,

557
00:34:30,235 --> 00:34:32,529
underneath tons of sand and dirt,

558
00:34:32,654 --> 00:34:34,322
and label them.

559
00:34:34,656 --> 00:34:37,075
You're about
as far from the stars as you can get.

560
00:34:42,789 --> 00:34:44,791
And you took her down with you.

561
00:34:46,042 --> 00:34:48,003
She was 19 years old.

562
00:34:58,221 --> 00:35:00,056
Go on then, kill me.

563
00:35:03,059 --> 00:35:04,603
Why are you doing this?

564
00:35:04,686 --> 00:35:08,023
I am armed. I will kill.

565
00:35:08,106 --> 00:35:11,151
It is my purpose.

566
00:35:11,234 --> 00:35:12,819
They're all dead because of you!

567
00:35:12,902 --> 00:35:16,406
They are dead because of us!

568
00:35:20,076 --> 00:35:21,536
And now what?

569
00:35:21,661 --> 00:35:23,163
What are you waiting for?

570
00:35:23,246 --> 00:35:28,001
I feel your fear.

571
00:35:28,877 --> 00:35:30,128
What do you expect?

572
00:35:30,211 --> 00:35:34,049
Daleks do not fear. Must not fear!

573
00:35:37,427 --> 00:35:40,305
You gave me life.

574
00:35:40,930 --> 00:35:45,226
What else have you given me?

575
00:35:45,310 --> 00:35:48,521
I am contaminated.

576
00:35:50,899 --> 00:35:52,984
You were quick on your feet,
leaving Rose behind.

577
00:35:53,068 --> 00:35:55,070
I'm not the one who sealed the vault!

578
00:35:55,195 --> 00:36:00,283
Open the bulkhead or Rose Tyler dies.

579
00:36:01,201 --> 00:36:02,410
(GASPS)

580
00:36:02,869 --> 00:36:04,162
You're alive!

581
00:36:04,245 --> 00:36:05,997
Can't get rid of me.

582
00:36:06,081 --> 00:36:07,707
I thought you were dead.

583
00:36:07,791 --> 00:36:10,001
Open the bulkhead!

584
00:36:10,418 --> 00:36:11,503
ROSE: Don't do it!

585
00:36:11,586 --> 00:36:14,547
What use are emotions,

586
00:36:14,631 --> 00:36:19,803
if you will not save the woman you love?

587
00:36:25,517 --> 00:36:27,268
I killed her once.

588
00:36:28,311 --> 00:36:29,604
I can't do it again.

589
00:36:47,539 --> 00:36:48,581
What do we do now?

590
00:36:48,665 --> 00:36:51,626
You bleeding heart, what the hell do we do?

591
00:36:51,710 --> 00:36:54,045
-Kill it when it gets here.
-All the guns are useless,

592
00:36:54,129 --> 00:36:55,422
and the alien weapons are in the vault.

593
00:36:55,505 --> 00:36:57,507
Only the catalogued ones.

594
00:37:01,928 --> 00:37:03,304
Broken.

595
00:37:04,764 --> 00:37:06,307
Broken.

596
00:37:06,599 --> 00:37:08,101
Hairdryer.

597
00:37:09,018 --> 00:37:11,271
Mr van Statten tends to dispose of his staff

598
00:37:11,354 --> 00:37:12,772
and when he does, he wipes their memory.

599
00:37:13,106 --> 00:37:15,650
I kept this stuff in case
I needed to fight my way out one day.

600
00:37:15,734 --> 00:37:16,735
What, you in a fight?

601
00:37:16,818 --> 00:37:18,069
-I'd like to see that.
-I could do!

602
00:37:18,153 --> 00:37:19,738
What you gonna do,
throw your A Levels at 'em?

603
00:37:19,821 --> 00:37:20,989
Oh, yes!

604
00:37:23,158 --> 00:37:24,826
Lock and load!

605
00:37:34,586 --> 00:37:36,463
I'm begging you, don't kill them.
You didn't kill me.

606
00:37:36,546 --> 00:37:37,839
But why not?

607
00:37:39,007 --> 00:37:41,259
Why are you alive?

608
00:37:41,843 --> 00:37:43,970
My function is to kill.

609
00:37:44,053 --> 00:37:45,972
What am I?

610
00:37:46,055 --> 00:37:47,766
What am I?

611
00:37:54,564 --> 00:37:56,816
Don't move! Don't do anything!

612
00:37:56,941 --> 00:37:58,568
It's beginning to question itself.

613
00:37:59,569 --> 00:38:01,029
Van Statten.

614
00:38:01,529 --> 00:38:03,573
You tortured me.

615
00:38:04,491 --> 00:38:05,867
Why?

616
00:38:05,950 --> 00:38:09,621
I wanted to help you, I just... I don't know,
I was trying to help.

617
00:38:09,704 --> 00:38:12,540
I thought if we could
get through to you, if we could mend you...

618
00:38:12,624 --> 00:38:14,292
I wanted you better. I'm sorry.

619
00:38:14,375 --> 00:38:17,879
I'm so sorry. I swear, I just wanted you to talk!

620
00:38:18,296 --> 00:38:20,799
Then hear me talk now.

621
00:38:20,882 --> 00:38:22,133
Exterminate!

622
00:38:22,217 --> 00:38:23,635
Exterminate!

623
00:38:23,718 --> 00:38:25,470
Exterminate!

624
00:38:25,553 --> 00:38:27,347
Don't do it! Don't kill him!

625
00:38:29,224 --> 00:38:31,059
You don't have to do this anymore.

626
00:38:31,142 --> 00:38:35,063
There must be something else,
not just killing. What else is there?

627
00:38:35,772 --> 00:38:36,981
What do you want?

628
00:38:43,404 --> 00:38:45,406
I want

629
00:38:45,490 --> 00:38:46,908
freedom.

630
00:39:28,074 --> 00:39:30,660
You're out. You made it.

631
00:39:34,247 --> 00:39:36,374
ROSE: I never thought
I'd feel the sunlight again.

632
00:39:36,457 --> 00:39:41,212
How does it feel?

633
00:39:43,298 --> 00:39:44,799
(WHIRRS)

634
00:40:17,248 --> 00:40:18,750
DOCTOR: Get out of the way!

635
00:40:23,004 --> 00:40:24,464
Rose, get out of the way, now!

636
00:40:24,547 --> 00:40:27,342
No! 'Cause I won't let you do this.

637
00:40:27,425 --> 00:40:29,427
That thing killed hundreds of people.

638
00:40:30,553 --> 00:40:32,180
It's not the one pointing the gun at me.

639
00:40:32,555 --> 00:40:35,016
I've got to do this. I've got to end it.

640
00:40:35,099 --> 00:40:37,852
The Daleks destroyed my home, my people.

641
00:40:37,936 --> 00:40:39,729
I've got nothing left.

642
00:40:39,812 --> 00:40:41,022
Look at it.

643
00:40:44,317 --> 00:40:45,360
What's it doing?

644
00:41:31,739 --> 00:41:38,746
I am the last of the Daleks.

645
00:41:39,914 --> 00:41:41,541
You're not even that.

646
00:41:43,710 --> 00:41:45,753
Rose did more than regenerate you.

647
00:41:46,421 --> 00:41:48,256
You've absorbed her DNA.

648
00:41:49,090 --> 00:41:50,341
You're mutating.

649
00:41:50,967 --> 00:41:53,928
Into what?

650
00:41:55,096 --> 00:41:56,431
Something new.

651
00:41:59,934 --> 00:42:01,227
I'm sorry.

652
00:42:01,310 --> 00:42:03,062
Isn't that better?

653
00:42:03,938 --> 00:42:05,314
Not for a Dalek.

654
00:42:06,524 --> 00:42:10,820
I can feel

655
00:42:10,903 --> 00:42:15,324
so many ideas.

656
00:42:15,408 --> 00:42:19,787
So much darkness.

657
00:42:19,871 --> 00:42:23,583
Rose. Give me orders.

658
00:42:25,543 --> 00:42:28,963
Order me to die.

659
00:42:33,801 --> 00:42:35,136
I can't do that.

660
00:42:35,261 --> 00:42:37,221
This is not life.

661
00:42:39,223 --> 00:42:41,642
This is sickness.

662
00:42:42,560 --> 00:42:46,022
I shall not be like you!

663
00:42:46,898 --> 00:42:48,983
Order my destruction!

664
00:42:51,444 --> 00:42:52,820
Obey!

665
00:42:52,945 --> 00:42:54,363
Obey!

666
00:42:54,447 --> 00:42:55,573
Obey!

667
00:42:59,035 --> 00:43:00,203
Do it.

668
00:43:02,663 --> 00:43:08,920
Are you frightened, Rose Tyler?

669
00:43:11,798 --> 00:43:13,007
Yeah.

670
00:43:14,801 --> 00:43:17,720
So am 1.

671
00:43:19,347 --> 00:43:22,725
Exterminate.

672
00:43:58,761 --> 00:43:59,887
What the hell are you doing?

673
00:44:00,012 --> 00:44:03,724
Two hundred personnel dead,
and all because of you, sir.

674
00:44:03,808 --> 00:44:07,395
Take him away, wipe his memory
and leave him by the road someplace.

675
00:44:07,478 --> 00:44:08,896
You can't do this to me!

676
00:44:08,980 --> 00:44:10,398
I am Henry van Statten!

677
00:44:10,565 --> 00:44:13,776
By tonight, Henry van Statten
will be a homeless, brainless junkie,

678
00:44:13,901 --> 00:44:17,822
living on the streets
of San Diego, Seattle, Sacramento.

679
00:44:18,656 --> 00:44:20,616
Some place beginning with "S."

680
00:44:25,246 --> 00:44:27,373
Little piece of home. Better than nothing.

681
00:44:27,957 --> 00:44:30,626
ROSE: Is that the end of it?
The Time War.

682
00:44:30,751 --> 00:44:31,919
I'm the only one left.

683
00:44:32,628 --> 00:44:35,047
I win. How about that?

684
00:44:36,007 --> 00:44:37,300
The Dalek survived.

685
00:44:37,383 --> 00:44:39,260
Maybe some of your people did, too.

686
00:44:39,343 --> 00:44:40,678
I'd know.

687
00:44:40,761 --> 00:44:41,888
In here.

688
00:44:43,014 --> 00:44:44,765
Feels like there's no one.

689
00:44:45,308 --> 00:44:47,935
Well, then. Good thing
I'm not going anywhere.

690
00:44:48,436 --> 00:44:49,478
Yeah.

691
00:44:49,604 --> 00:44:50,938
We'd better get out.

692
00:44:51,272 --> 00:44:53,816
Van Statten's disappeared.
They're closing down the base.

693
00:44:54,025 --> 00:44:55,860
ADAM: Goddard says
they're gonna fill it full of cement,

694
00:44:55,943 --> 00:44:57,069
like it never existed!

695
00:44:57,153 --> 00:44:58,237
It's about time.

696
00:44:58,946 --> 00:45:00,114
I'll have to go back home.

697
00:45:00,198 --> 00:45:01,240
Better hurry up, then.

698
00:45:01,324 --> 00:45:03,534
Next flight to Heathrow leaves at 1500 hours.

699
00:45:03,618 --> 00:45:06,746
Adam was saying
that all his life, he wanted to see the stars.

700
00:45:07,288 --> 00:45:08,956
Tell him to go and stand outside, then.

701
00:45:09,624 --> 00:45:12,043
He's all on his own, Doctor. And he did help.

702
00:45:12,126 --> 00:45:13,461
He left you down there!

703
00:45:13,544 --> 00:45:14,587
So did you.

704
00:45:14,670 --> 00:45:16,464
What are you talking about?
We've got to leave!

705
00:45:16,797 --> 00:45:18,216
Plus, he's a bit pretty.

706
00:45:18,299 --> 00:45:19,592
I hadn't noticed.

707
00:45:21,427 --> 00:45:22,511
On your own head.

708
00:45:22,595 --> 00:45:25,681
What are you doing? She said cement.

709
00:45:25,973 --> 00:45:28,726
She wasn't joking, we're gonna get sealed in!

710
00:45:30,561 --> 00:45:31,771
Doctor?

711
00:45:32,313 --> 00:45:35,149
What are you doing standing inside a box?

712
00:45:37,777 --> 00:45:38,945
Rose?

713
00:45:41,781 --> 00:45:43,157
(WHOOSHING)

714
00:45:53,167 --> 00:45:55,544
The fourth great and bountiful human empire.

715
00:45:55,836 --> 00:45:57,338
Planet Earth at its height.

716
00:45:59,590 --> 00:46:02,301
Kronkburger with cheese,
kronkburger with pa jatos.

717
00:46:02,385 --> 00:46:03,719
Something's wrong.

718
00:46:04,303 --> 00:46:06,013
My watch must be wrong.

719
00:46:06,097 --> 00:46:07,265
That's what comes with showing off.

720
00:46:07,348 --> 00:46:08,724
Your history's not as good
as you thought it was.

721
00:46:08,849 --> 00:46:09,934
My history's perfect.

722
00:46:10,017 --> 00:46:11,269
Well, obviously not.

723
00:46:11,352 --> 00:46:12,812
I can taste it.

724
00:46:12,895 --> 00:46:14,272
Engage safety.

725
00:46:14,355 --> 00:46:16,315
MAN: Someone down there
shouldn't be here.

726
00:46:19,986 --> 00:46:21,279
WOMAN: Who are you?

727
00:46:21,362 --> 00:46:23,072
I'm the editor.

728
00:46:23,155 --> 00:46:24,198
What's happening?

729
00:46:24,407 --> 00:46:25,700
And spike.

730
00:46:29,328 --> 00:46:30,454
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

